HORIZONWORKS DIVERSITY, EQUITY & INCLUSION
2025-2026 Initiative Summary

===========================================
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
===========================================

HorizonWorks is committed to building a workplace where everyone can thrive. This document outlines our DEI initiatives, progress, and goals for 2025-2026.

===========================================
OUR DEI PILLARS
===========================================

1. DIVERSE HIRING
   - Blind resume screening for initial candidate review
   - Diverse interview panels required for all roles
   - Partnerships with HBCUs and Hispanic-Serving Institutions
   - Apprenticeship program for career changers
   - Goal: 45% of new hires from underrepresented groups (currently 42%)

2. INCLUSIVE CULTURE
   - Mandatory inclusive leadership training for all managers
   - Anonymous feedback channels monitored weekly
   - Regular culture surveys with DEI-specific questions
   - Accessibility audit of all offices and digital tools completed
   - Pronoun options in all internal systems

3. EQUITABLE ADVANCEMENT
   - Pay equity audit conducted annually (last audit: November 2025)
   - Sponsorship program pairing senior leaders with high-potential URG employees
   - Promotion criteria documented and published internally
   - Manager training on recognizing and mitigating bias in reviews

4. COMMUNITY & BELONGING
   - 6 active Employee Resource Groups (see separate document)
   - Monthly heritage and awareness celebrations
   - DEI book club and discussion groups
   - Community volunteer partnerships

===========================================
2025 PROGRESS HIGHLIGHTS
===========================================

- Closed gender pay gap to within 1% across all levels
- Increased URG representation in leadership from 28% to 34%
- Launched neurodiversity hiring pilot program
- 94% of managers completed inclusive leadership training
- All offices now have gender-neutral restrooms and lactation rooms

===========================================
2026 PRIORITIES
===========================================

1. Expand apprenticeship program to engineering (currently sales/marketing only)
2. Launch veteran hiring initiative
3. Achieve 40% URG representation in senior leadership
4. Complete accessibility certification for all customer-facing products
5. Pilot "returnship" program for caregivers re-entering workforce

